title: Fagus sylvatica "purpurea tricolor" (rosepink European beech) 6
description: Fagus sylvatica "purpurea tricolor" - rosepink European beech (Dawes Arboretum, Licking County, Ohio, USA) The rosepink European beech tree is a manmade cultivar (cultivated variety) of European beech, which is native to much of mainland Europe, parts of southern Britain, and parts of southern Scandinavia. Classification: Plantae, Angiospermophyta, Fagales, Fagaceae ------------------------------ Info. at: en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fagus_sylvatica and en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beech
